description.1: It's villain revenge night! Two of Spidey's old foes, the Gibbon and the Beetle, are out for wall-crawler blood!
description.2: While starting over as She-Hulk, the green giantess is attacked by the Seeker!
description.3: It's Daredevil and Elektra against the Hand and the Hand's master assassin Kiringi! Will DD be able to give it his all with his radar sense on the fritz?
description.4: Ghost Rider comes upon a town with a severe water shortage. You can never find a Water Wizard when you need one…
description.5: Tony is deeply depressed following Bethany's voluntary "departure." Due to a caustic spill at GARD, Scott Lang as Ant-Man must save the day.
description.7: Tyr arrives in Asgard and demands Sif's love! Meanwhile, Donald Blake faces some professional woes at his clinic...what will happen when both his worlds collide?
description.8: What would happen if Earth's Mightiest Heroes had not an enemy in sight? In fact, what if the Avengers were the only super heroes standing? Uatu postulates the near impossible!
description.9: Thing is on a mission to destroy Ego the Living Planet! But why? And can he complete his mission without being mind-controlled by Ego?
description.10: The X-Men take on their greatest nemesis Magneto, but will they have to resort to killing him once and for all?
description.12: Samson Scythe pays the ultimate price for his involvement in a Coast Guard ship's explosion! Cap trails crime boss Sean Gamble to learn more about the demise of Carlo Ferrini.
description.13: A rendezvous with REVENGE! The Ghost Rider is in town, but Johnny Blaze has lost control of his fiery form! Can the Thing help get the Spirit of Vengeance back under Blaze's control?
description.15: The Doctor and Clea take part in some leisure, unaware that Baron Mordo lies in wait. Writer Morgana Blessing requests Stephen's counsel on her next fiction about mysticism.
description.16: Dazzler's employer has been kidnapped, and it's looking to be a challenging rescue!
description.17: Spider-Man meets a worthy adversary in the cyborg Ramrod. Spidey saves some of his fellow students during Ramrod's on-campus attack, but must don the mask again during a night out in Brooklyn! An entire bar of people start behaving violently after a free round of beer, and Peter suspects the drinks have been laced with a mood-altering agent!
description.18: A lover's quarrel between two immortal beings threatens the entirety of D.C. Meet Linnea, the Elf queen in exile, who dukes it out with her warrior mate, Gorn. Gorn, humiliated by Linnea's expansive power, strikes her. Why are the Avengers involved? Good question!
description.19: He's twice as big and twice as much trouble! Don't miss this issue as Captain America takes on the power-mad Ameridroid!
description.24: The Rebels infiltrate the Imperial superweapon Tarkin with the intention of sabotaging it!
description.26: Ka-Zar... versus his dad? This is one family reunion that’s looking to be a nightmare.
description.27: MEPHISTO tips his hand! Revealed as the true leader of the Six-Fingered Hand, he and his demonic comrades have devised a plan to make Earth a living hell, and only the Defenders can stop him!
description.28: Spider-Man tangles with the super-criminal known as the Ringer - but beats him easily…TOO easily. Someone is lurking in the shadows behind this fishy ambush, and Peter aims to find out who!
description.29: Jennifer decides to remain in her She-Hulk form and abandon life as Jennifer Walters!
description.30: Kingpin hires the hand to eliminate Daredevil. Plus, Murdock loses his radar sense!
description.31: Ghost Rider is beset by evil magic…can he save a train from exploding or will the magic overwhelm him?
description.32: Los Angeles faces the rumblings of Avalanche and Landslide! Can Hulk find his footing against these quake-inducing foes?
description.33: Iron Man and Doctor Doom are trapped in the past, and they now find themselves in the fabled court of Camelot! In order to return to the present Doctor Doom and Iron Man must strike a truce. Featuring Morgan Le Fay.
description.34: A young man is shot outside of Donald Blake's clinic, causing an all-out race war in New York City. Can Blake use his influence as Thor to restore peace?
description.35: Skip Collins is on a tour of New York- the day the city comes crumbling down! Can this ordinary man with an ordinary life save New York in an extraordinary way?
description.36: When the X-Men arrive at Magneto's abandoned Antarctic base, they find it's not so abandoned.  Garokk is there to ward off intruders, especially the X-Men.
description.40: The Hulk is on a rampage and people are in danger! Can Dazzler stop him and bring back Banner to his senses?
description.41: Shanna falls to the influence of the mind-swapping machine! Does she truly have feelings for Dherk?
description.46: A Moon Knight-centric issue! Moon Knight steals some expensive loot to become the secretary of the National Crime Syndicate Directorate. Peter's on an assignment with the Bugle to get photos of the elusive Mr. Knight, but he may have more luck encountering him as Spider-Man. Spider-Man and Moon Knight team-up to take down a gang of overzealous crooks!
description.47: When Captain America holds an open call for Avengers applicants, the mansion is swarmed by X-Men, former members, anti-heroes, and a cat-woman named Tigra. Tigra's introductory issue as member of the Avengers!
description.48: When Captain America makes a trip to California, he's greeted by the resident hero, Nomad! Can Cap and Nomad team up together to stop the rising crime in the City of Angels?
description.51: The construction of a new Imperial superweapon may mean the end for the Rebellion.
description.52: The city of Citrusville, Florida has vanished! The Defenders confront the Six-Fingered Hand, but the evil cult has a few new friends under their control - Hulk, Namor, and the Silver Surfer!
description.54: When a fancy dinner event goes horribly wrong, only one man stands between innocent people and certain doom -- J. Jonah Jameson!?
description.55: Jennifer finds herself having control issues over She-Hulk!
description.56: What if Daredevil, Man Without Fear, was an agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.? 'Nuff said!
description.59: Spider-Man teams up with a multitude of heroes including Quasar, Thing, Scarlet Witch and Dr. Strange against a supernatural threat!
description.60: Tongah, Ka-Zar's best friend, is ill with a deadly disease easily treated by modern medicine. Will Ka-Zar be able to help him, or will he lose his best friend?
description.63: Strange vs. the diabolical Damballah! Morgana Blessing makes her first appearance, showing off a connection to the occult that may aid Strange later.
description.64: Dazzler's got the band together and they are ready to perform. The show's about to start and the Hulk busts in… and he's MAD!
description.65: What is the Crimson Fever and why is it so deadly that it forces Luke and the others to stop their pursuit of the captured Han in order to stop it?
description.69: Daredevil is on the hunt for the man who crippled Becky Blake.
description.70: Has Ghost Rider jumped the shark? No, he's caught in a wave of evil, between the mighty magic of Moondark and the Water Wizard.
description.71: Bruce spends a month with the beautiful Glazier at her glass home in Malibu. But will Hulk's dreams shatter when Glazier takes their friendship to the next level?
description.72: Featuring Dr. Doom and his resentful stooge, Hauptman! After stopping a terrorist cell from stealing cargo on a Stark International barge, Iron Man must head into Latverian waters to get to the source of the organization.
description.74: The demon Mephisto has conquered an entire New York City block...and has dragged its residents down to his domain! The God of Thunder springs into action.
description.75: Johnny launches his own investigation into the murder of one of his old high school bullies. How's the Maggia involved?
description.76: It's Girls Night Out, but when Kitty disappears, will they find a new threat or a new ally?  Plus, Cyclops is confronted by the master of magnetism Magneto!
description.78: Guest-starring Matt Murdock, attorney without fear! Spider-Man needs a strong defense after breaking into Ryker's Island to investigate recent escapes. Why are super-powered villains breaking out of prison with relative ease? Imprisoned behind bars, this is one undercover assignment Peter Parker can't walk away from!
description.79: With the world's weather running amok, the Avengers must find the source of the natural disturbances. Will the answer to the catastrophic weather patterns be found in Argentina, or Antarctica?
description.80: What happens when the Sentinel of Liberty finds himself behind bars? You don't want to miss this issue!
description.81: Devil-Slayer confronts the Defenders with a mission to rescue his wife from a strange cult she has been following in Israel. But where did this cult come from, and who is their mysterious leader known only as the Messiah?
description.82: Havoc at the hospital! Jack-O-Lantern has taken hostages, and it's up to Spider-Man to take him down!
description.83: She-Hulk must stop the Grappler from getting his hands on a truck full of gold!
description.84: Thinking his wife is dead, Kingpin takes control of the mob and hires Bullseye as his assassin.
description.85: Evil is the Enforcer! And Ghost Rider cannot abide evil.
description.86: Bruce Banner is met by an old foe upon his arrival at Easter Island- the Absorbing Man attacks!
description.87: Innocent lives are at stake when Stark International's Central America plant is under siege!
description.88: Thor and Amos thwart an attack on the Savoy Hotel!
description.89: Fighting fire with fire! The Fantastic Four are attacked by the four elements: Earth, Air, Fire and Water! Meanwhile, Johnny and Frankie Raye rekindle their old fling. Will she finally accept his hero alter-ego?
description.90: The X-Men still find themselves unwilling vistors of Castle Doom and it will be up to Storm to take a risky endevor in order to escape.
description.92: The rise of Mud-Thing! After Spider-Man tosses Sandman and Hydro-man off the docks, the two villains merge into one horrific sand-mud monstrosity. Will New York ever be safe from the wrath of Mud-Thing? Sadie Frickett takes it to court to defend the men she loves, but ends up promoting Mud-Thing in their own Broadway revue! Think that's the strangest thing to happen in this issue? Think again!
description.93: The Beast rekindles his romance with Vera Cantor, an old flame from his days at the Xavier Institute. But after Vera is poisoned y a rogue cup o' tea, will the Skrulls step in and save her life?
description.94: The Star-Spangled Avenger is sent to go find the son of Ray Coulson, who has recently joined a biker gang. It is here that Captain America learns that Doc Ock has been following him. Can Cap defeat the Doc Ock and the gang without his shield?
description.95: Can Luke and Leia return a prince back to his planet before his younger brother, an Imperial sympathizer, will gain control of the planet?
description.98: See the secret life of Jean Grey, The Phoenix!
description.99: Leanne switches into Shanna’s body -- and is helpless against a dinosaur attack!
